.TH SIMPLE_SHELL 1 "November 2025" "Holberton School" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
simple_shell \- simple UNIX command interpreter
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B simple_shell
.RI [command_file]
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B simple_shell
program is a basic command interpreter that reads commands from standard input or from a file and executes them.
It provides a prompt, executes commands found in the system PATH, and includes a few built-in commands.
.SH BUILTINS
.TP
.B exit
Exit the shell.
.TP
.B env
Print the current environment.
.SH RETURN VALUE
Returns the exit status of the last command executed.
.SH EXAMPLES
Run in interactive mode:
.RS
.nf
$ ./hsh
($) /bin/ls
($) exit
.fi
.RE
Run in non-interactive mode:
.RS
.nf
$ echo "ls -l" | ./hsh
.fi
.RE
.SH AUTHORS
Written by Thekira A. Ahmed <11968@holbertonstudents.com>
and Yara K. Alrasheed <11982@holbertonstudents.com>.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR sh (1)
